obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (16365)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16365&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prasar Bharati`
  line `(Broadcasting Corporation of India) Act, 1990.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 15th September, 1997, vide notification No. S.O. 509(E), dated 22nd July, 1997, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (16366)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16366&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Akashvani" means the offices, stations and other establishments, by whatever name called,`
  line `which, immediately before the appointed day, formed part of or were under the Director-General,`
  line `All India Radio of the Union Ministry of Information and Broadcasting;`
  line
  line `(b) "appointed day" means the date appointed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "broadcasting" means the dissemination of any form of communication like signs, signals,`
  line `writing, pictures, images and sounds of all kinds by transmission of electro-magnetic waves through`
  line `space or through cables intended to be received by the general public either directly or indirectly`
  line `through the medium of relay stations and all its grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall`
  line `be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(d) "Board" means the Prasar Bharati Board;`
  line
  line `(e) "Broadcasting Council" means the Council established under section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Corporation appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(g) "Corporation" means the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India) established under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(h) "Doordarshan" means the offices, kendras and other establishments, by whatever name called,`
  line `which, immediately before the appointed day, formed part of or were under the Directorate-General,`
  line `Doordarshan of the Union Ministry of Information and Broadcasting;`
  line
  line `(i) "elected Member" means a Member elected under section 3;`
  line
  line `(j) "Executive Member" means the Executive Member appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(k) "kendra" means any telecasting centre with studios or transmitters or both and includes a relay`
  line station;
  line
  line `(l) "Member" means a Member of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) "Member (Finance)" means the Member (Finance) appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(n) "Member (Personnel)" means the Member (Personnel) appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(o) "Nominated Member" means the Member nominated by the Union Ministry of Information`
  line `and Broadcasting under section 3;`
  line
  line `(p) "Non-lapsable Fund" means the Fund created from the commercial revenues of Akashvani`
  line `and Doordarshan to meet expenditure on certain schemes;`
  line
  line `(q) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(r) "Part-time Member" means a Part-time Member of the Board appointed under section 4, but`
  line `does not include an ex officio Member, the Nominated Member or an elected Member;`
  line
  line `(s) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) "Recruitment Board" means a board established under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(u) "regulations" means regulations made by the Corporation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) "station" means any broadcasting station with studios or transmitters or both and includes a`
  line `relay station;`
  line
  line `(w) "Whole-time Member" means the Executive Member, Member (Finance) or`
  line `Member (Personnel);`
  line
  line `(x) "year" means the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (16367)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and composition of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16367&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may by notification appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for the purposes of this`
  line `Act a Corporation, to be known as the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India).`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal with power to acquire,hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The headquarters of the Corporation shall be at New Delhi and the Corporation may establish`
  line `offices, kendras or stations at other places in India and, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government,outside India.`
  line
  line `(4) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the Corporation shall vest`
  line `in the Prasar Bharati Board which may exercise all such powers and do all such acts and things as may be`
  line `exercised or done by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) one Executive Member;`
  line
  line `(c) one Member(Finance);`
  line
  line `(d) one Member(Personnel);`
  line
  line `(e) six Part-time Members;`
  line
  line `(f) Director-General(Akashvani), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) Director-General (Doordarshan), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) one representative of the Union Ministry of Information and Broadcasting, to be nominated by`
  line `that Ministry; and`
  line
  line `(i) two representatives of the employees of the Corporation, of whom one shall be elected by the`
  line `engineering staff from amongst themselves and one shall be elected by the other employees from`
  line `amongst themselves.`
  line
  line `(6) The Corporation may appoint such committees as may be necessary for the efficient performance,`
  line `exercise and discharge of its functions, powers and duties:`
  line
  line `Provided that all or a majority of the members of each committee shall be Members and a member of`
  line `any such committee who is not a Member shall have only the right to attend meetings of the committee`
  line `and take part in the proceedings thereof, but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be`
  line `provided by regulations, any person whoseassistance or advice it may need in complying with any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the`
  line `Board relevant to the purposes of which he has been associated, but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(8) No act or proceeding of the Board or of any committee appointed by it under sub-section (6) shall`
  line `be invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of,the Board or such committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member or a member of such`
  line committee;or
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or such committee not affecting the merits of the`
  line case.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (16368)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Chairman and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16368&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman and the other Members,`
  line `except the ex officio Members, the Nominated Member and the elected Members shall be appointed by`
  line `the President of India on the recommendation of a committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the Council of States, who shall be the Chairman of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairman of the Press Council of India established under section 4 of the Press Council`
  line `Act, 1978(37 of 1978); and`
  line
  line `(c) one nominee of the President of India.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of a Member shall be invalidated merely by reason of any vacancy in, or any`
  line `defect in the constitution of, the committee appointed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman and the Part-time Members shall be persons of eminence in public life; the`
  line `Executive Member shall be a person having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of such`
  line `matters as administration, management, broadcasting, education, literature, culture, arts, music, dramatics`
  line `or journalism; the Member (Finance) shall be a person having special knowledge or practical experience`
  line `in respect of financial matters and the Member (Personnel) shall be a person having special knowledge or`
  line `practical experience in respect of personnel management and administration.`
  line
  line `(4) The recommendations made by the committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall be binding`
  line `for the purposes of appointment under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (16369)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers and functions of Executive Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16369&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `TheExecutive Member shall be the Chief`
  line `Executive of the Corporation and shall,subject to the control and supervision of the Board, exercise such`
  line `powers anddischarge such functions of the Board as it may delegate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (16370)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office, conditions of service, etc., of Chairman and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16370&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The`
  line `Chairman shall be Part-time Member and shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on`
  line `which he enters upon his office or until he attains the age of seventy years, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person holding office as a Chairman immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India) Amendment Act, 2008 (12 of 2008) shall, in so far as`
  line `his appointment is inconsistent with the provisions of this sub-section, cease to hold office on such`
  line `commencement as such Chairman and shall not be entitled to any compensation because of his ceasing to`
  line `hold such office.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^1`
  line `*** the Member (Finance) and the Member (Personnel) shall be Whole-time Members and every`
  line `such Member shall hold office for a term of six years from the date on which he enters upon his office or`
  line `until he attains the age of sixty-two years, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2A) The Executive Member shall be a Whole-time Member and shall hold office for a term of`
  line `five years from the date on which he enters upon his office or until he attains the age of sixty-five years,`
  line `whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person holding office as an Executive Member immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India) Amendment Act, 2008`
  line `(12 of 2008), shall, in so far as his appointment is inconsistent with the provisions of this sub-section,`
  line `cease to hold office on such commencement as such Executive Member and shall not be entitled to any`
  line `compensation because of his ceasing to hold such office.]`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of Part-time Members shall be six years, but one-third of such Members shall`
  line `retire on the expiration of every second year.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of an elected Member shall be two years or till he ceases to be an employee of`
  line `the Corporation, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(5) As soon as may be after the establishment of the Corporation, the President of India may, by`
  line `order, make such provision as he thinks fit for curtailing the term of office of some of the Part-time`
  line `Members then appointed in order that one-third of the Members holding office as such Part-time`
  line `Members shall retire in every second year thereafter.`
  line
  line `(6) Where before the expiry of the term of office of a person holding the office of Chairman, or any`
  line `other Member, a vacancy arises, for any reason whatsoever, such vacancy shall be deemed to be a casual`
  line `vacancy and the person appointed or elected to fill such vacancy shall hold office for the unexpired period`
  line `of the term for which his predecessor in office would have held office if such vacancy had not arisen.`
  line
  line `(7) The Whole-time Members shall be the employees of the Corporation and as such shall be entitled`
  line `to such salaries and allowances and shall be subject to such conditions of service in respect of leave,`
  line `pension (if any), provident fund and other matters as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salaries and allowances and the conditions of service shall not be varied to their`
  line `disadvantage after their appointment.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chairman and Part-time Members shall be entitled to such allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 12 of 2008, s.2,for sub-section (1) (w.e.f .7-2-2008).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-2-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (16371)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal and suspension of Chairman and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16371&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), the Chairman or any other Member,except an ex officio Member, the Nominated Member`
  line `and an elected Member, shall only be removed from his office by order of the President of India on the`
  line `ground of misbehavior after the Supreme Court, on a reference being made to it by the President, has, on`
  line `inquiry held in accordance with such procedure as the Supreme Court may by rules provide, reported that`
  line `the Chairman or such other Member, as the case may be, ought, on such ground, be removed.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may suspend from office the Chairman or other Member except an ex officio`
  line `Member, the Nominated Member or an elected Member, in respect of whom a reference has been made to`
  line `the Supreme Court under sub-section (1) until the President has passed orders on receipt of the report of`
  line `the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(3)Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the President may, by order, remove the`
  line `Chairman or any Whole-time Member from his office if such Chairman or such Whole-time Member--`
  line
  line `(a) ceases to be a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(d) is convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude;or`
  line
  line `(e) is, in the opinion of the President, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of body or`
  line `mind:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President may, by order, remove any Part-time Member from his office if he is`
  line `adjudged an insolvent or is convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude or where he is, in the`
  line `opinion of the President, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of body or mind.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Chairman or any Whole-time Member, except any ex officio Member, the Nominated`
  line `Member or any elected Member, is, or becomes in anyway concerned or interested in any contract or`
  line `agreement made by or on behalf of the Corporation or the Government of India or the Government of a`
  line `State or,participates in any way in the profit thereof, or in any benefit or emolument arising therefrom than`
  line `as a member, and in common with other members of an incorporated company, he shall, for the purposes`
  line `of sub-section (1), be deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
  line
  line `(5) If a Part-time Member is, or becomes in any way concerned, or interested in any contract or`
  line `agreement made by or on behalf of the Corporation, he shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairman or any other Member may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the`
  line `President of India and on such resignation being accepted, the Chairman or other Member shall be deemed`
  line `to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (16372)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16372&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `meetings) as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall not be less than six meetings every year but three months shall not intervene`
  line `between one meeting and the next meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) A Member shall be deemed to have vacated his office if he absents himself for three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Board without the leave of the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman shall preside at the meetings of the Board and if for any reason he is unable to`
  line `attend any meeting, the Executive Member and in the absence of both, any other Member elected by the`
  line `Members present at such meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `the votes of the Members present and voting and, in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or in`
  line `his absence, the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (16373)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers and other employees of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16373&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such control, restrictions and`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, the Corporation may appoint, after consultation with the Recruitment`
  line `Board, the Director-General (Akashvani), the Director-General (Doordarshan) and such other officers and`
  line `other employees as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The method of recruitment of such officers and employees and all other matters connected`
  line `therewith and the conditions of service of such officers and other employees shall be such as may be`
  line `provided by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (16374)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Establishment of Recruitment Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16374&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) the Corporation shall, as soon as may be, after the`
  line `appointed day and in such manner and subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed,`
  line `establish for the purposes of section 9, one or more Recruitment Boards consisting wholly of persons`
  line `other than the Members, officers and other employees of the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of appointment to the posts carrying scales of pay which are not less`
  line `than that of a Joint Secretary to the Central Government, the Recruitment Board shall consist of the`
  line `Chairman, other Members, the ex officio Members, the Nominated Member and the elected Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications and other conditions of service of the members constituting the Recruitment`
  line `Board and the period for which such members shall hold office, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (16375)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Status of officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 2012, s. 2, for section 11 (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16375&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Status of officers and employees.--(1) All officers and employees recruited for the purposes of`
  line `Akashvani or Doordarshan before the appointed day and in service in the Corporation as on the 1st day of April, 2000, shall be on deemed deputation to the Corporation with effect from the 1st day of April, 2000,`
  line `and shall so continue till their retirement.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers and employees recruited during the period on or after the appointed day till the`
  line `5th day of October, 2007, shall be on deemed deputation to the Corporation with effect from the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2000 or the date of their joining service in the Corporation, whichever is later and until their`
  line retirement.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), "officers and employees recruited" means`
  line `officers and employees recruited either under the proviso to article 309 of the Constitution or in`
  line `accordance with the regulations made under the Act, but shall not include persons engaged or appointed`
  line `on daily wages, casual, ad hoc or work charged basis.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers and employees referred to in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) shall be entitled to`
  line `the pay and all other benefits as admissible to an employee of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officers and employees shall not be entitled to any deputation allowance.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Corporation`
  line `shall have the disciplinary and supervisory powers and full control on the officers and employees referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), including the power to transfer them from one place, post or`
  line `media to another, and to suspend, initiate disciplinary proceedings and impose major or minor penalties:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power to impose major penalties of compulsory retirement, removal or dismissal`
  line `from service shall be exercised by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) All officers and employees recruited after the 5th day of October, 2007 shall be officers and`
  line `employees of the Corporation and shall be governed by such conditions of service as may be specified in`
  line `the regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (16376)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Section 11 not to apply to certain officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 2012, s. 2, for section 11 (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16376&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Section 11 not to apply to certain officers and employees.--(1) The provisions of section 11`
  line `shall not apply to officers and employees of the Indian Information Service, the Central Secretariat`
  line `Service or any other service borne on any cadre outside Akashvani or Doordarshan, who have been`
  line `working in Akashvani or Doordarshan before the appointed day or in service in the Corporation after that`
  line day.
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service in the Corporation of officers and employees referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (16377)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer of posts of Akashvani and Doordarshan to Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 2012, s. 2, for section 11 (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16377&sectionno=11B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Transfer of posts of Akashvani and Doordarshan to Corporation.--(1) All posts in the`
  line `erstwhile Akashvani and Doordarshan other than the posts borne on the strength of the cadres referred to`
  line `insub-section (2) shall be deemed to have been transferred to the Corporation with effect from the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2000.`
  line
  line `(2) All matters relating to the posts borne on the strength of the cadres of the Indian Information`
  line `Service, the Central Secretariat Service or any other cadre outside Akashvani or Doordarshan, in so far as`
  line `such posts are concerned with the Corporation, shall be determined in such manner and on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (16378)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions and powers of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16378&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, it shall be the`
  line `primary duty of the Corporation to organise and conduct public broadcasting services to inform, educate`
  line `and entertain the public and to ensure a balanced development of broadcasting on radio and television.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this section shall`
  line `be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the provisions of the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885(13 of 1985).`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall, in the discharge of its functions, be guided by the following objectives,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) upholding the unity and integrity of the country and the values enshrined in the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) safeguarding the citizen's right to be informed freely, truthfully and objectively on all matters`
  line `of public interest, national or international, and presenting a fair and balanced flow of information`
  line `including contrasting views without advocating any opinion or ideology of its own;`
  line
  line `(c) paying special attention to the fields of education and spread of literacy, agriculture, rural`
  line `development, environment, health and family welfare and science and technology;`
  line
  line `(d) providing adequate coverage to the diverse cultures and languages of the various regions of`
  line `the country by broadcasting appropriate programmes;`
  line
  line `(e) providing adequate coverage to sports and games so as to encourage healthy competition and`
  line `the spirit of sportsmanship;`
  line
  line `(f) providing appropriate programmes keeping in view the special needs of the youth;`
  line
  line `(g) informing and stimulating the national consciousness in regard to the status and problems of`
  line `women and paying special attention to the upliftment of women;`
  line
  line `(h) promoting social justice and combating exploitation, inequality and such evils as`
  line `untouchability and advancing the welfare of the weaker sections of the society;`
  line
  line `(i) safeguarding the rights of the working classes and advancing their welfare;`
  line
  line `(j) serving the rural and weaker sections of the people and those residing in border regions,`
  line `backward or remote areas;`
  line
  line `(k) providing suitable programmes keeping in view the special needs of the minorities and tribal`
  line communities;
  line
  line `(l) taking special steps to protect the interests of children, the blind, the aged, the handicapped`
  line `and other vulnerable sections of the people;`
  line
  line `(m) promoting national integration by broadcasting in a manner that facilitates communication in`
  line `the languages in India;`
  line `and facilitating the distribution of regional broadcasting services in every State`
  line `in the languages of that State;`
  line
  line `(n) providing comprehensive broadcast coverage through the choice of appropriate technology`
  line `and the best utilisation of the broadcast frequencies available and ensuring high quality reception;`
  line
  line `(o) promoting research and development activities in order to ensure that radio and television`
  line `broadcast technology are constantly updated; and`
  line
  line `(p) expanding broadcasting facilities by establishing additional channels of transmission at`
  line `various levels.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the Corporation`
  line `may take such steps as it thinks fit--`
  line
  line `(a) to ensure that broadcasting is conducted as a public service to provide and produce`
  line programmes;
  line
  line `(b) to establish a system for the gathering of news for radio and television;`
  line
  line `(c) to negotiate for purchase of, or otherwise acquire, programmes and rights or privileges in`
  line `respect of sports and other events, films, serials, occasions, meetings, functions or incidents of public`
  line `interest, for broadcasting and to establish procedures for the allocation of such programmes, rights or`
  line `privileges to the services;`
  line
  line `(d) to establish and maintain a library or libraries of radio, television and other materials;`
  line
  line `(e) to conduct or commission, from time to time, programmes, audience research, market or`
  line `technical service, which may be released to such persons and in such manner and subject to such`
  line `terms and conditions as the Corporation may think fit;`
  line
  line `(f) to provide such other services as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-sections (2) and (3) shall prevent the Corporation from managing on behalf of the`
  line `Central Government and in accordance with such terms and conditions as may be specified by that`
  line `Government the broadcasting of External Services and monitoring of broadcasts made by organisations`
  line `outside India on the basis of arrangements made for reimbursement of expenses by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of ensuring that adequate time is made available for the promotion of the`
  line `objectives set out in this section, the Central Governmentshall have the power to determine the maximum`
  line `limit of broadcast time in respect of the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(6) The Corporation shall be subject to no civil liability on the ground merely that it failed to comply`
  line `with any of the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation shall have power to determine and levy fees and other service charges for or in`
  line `respect of the advertisements and such programmes as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fees and other service charges levied and collected under this sub-section shall not`
  line `exceed such limits as may be determined by the Central Government, from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (16379)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Parliamentary Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16379&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Committee consisting of`
  line `twenty-two Members of Parliament, of whom fifteen from the House of the People to be elected by the`
  line `Members thereof and seven from the Council of States to be elected by the Members thereof in`
  line `accordance with the system of proportional representation by means of the single transferable vote, to`
  line `oversee that the Corporation discharges its functions in accordance with the provisions of this Act and, in`
  line `particular, the objectives set out in section 12 and submit a report thereon to Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall function in accordance with such rules as may be made by the Speaker of the`
  line `House of the People.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (16380)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Establishment of Broadcasting Council, term of office and removal, etc., of members thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16380&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established, by notification, as soon as may be after the appointed day, a`
  line `Council, to be known as the Broadcasting Council, to receive and consider complaints referred to in`
  line `section 15 and to advise the Corporation in the discharge of its functions in accordance with the`
  line `objectives set out in section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The Broadcasting Council shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(i) a President and ten other members to be appointed by the President of India from amongst`
  line `persons of eminence in public life;`
  line
  line `(ii) four Members of Parliament, of whom two from the House of the People to be nominated by`
  line `the Speaker thereof and two from the Council of States to be nominated by the Chairman thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The President of the Broadcasting Council shall be a whole-time member and every other member`
  line `shall be a part-time member and the President or the part-time member shall hold office as such for a term`
  line `of three years from the date on which he enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(4) The Broadcasting Council may constitute such number of Regional Councils as it may deem`
  line `necessary to aid and assist the Council in the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(5) The President of the Broadcasting Council shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and`
  line `shall be subject to such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension (if any), provident fund and`
  line `other matters as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salary and allowances and the conditions of service shall not be varied to the`
  line `disadvantage of the President of the Broadcasting Council after his appointment.`
  line
  line `(6) The other members of the Broadcasting Council and the members of the Regional Councils`
  line `constituted under sub-section (4) shall be entitled to such allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (16381)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Jurisdiction of, and the procedure to be followed by, Broadcasting Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16381&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Broadcasting Council shall receive and consider complaints from--`
  line
  line `(i) any person or group of persons alleging that a certain programme or broadcast or the`
  line `functioning of the Corporation in specific cases or in general is not in accordance with the objectives`
  line `for which the Corporation is established;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person (other than an officer or employee of the Corporation) claiming himself to have`
  line `been treated unjustly or unfairly in any manner (including unwarranted invasion of privacy,`
  line `misrepresentation, distortion or lack of objectivity) in connection with any programme broadcast by`
  line `the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) A complaint under sub-section (1) shall be made in such manner and within such period as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Broadcasting Council shall follow such procedure as it thinks fit for the disposal of`
  line `complaints received by it.`
  line
  line `(4) If the complaint is found to be justified either wholly or in part, the Broadcasting Council shall`
  line `advise the Executive Member to take appropriate action.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Executive Member is unable to accept the recommendation of the Broadcasting Council, he`
  line `shall place such recommendation before the Board for its decision thereon.`
  line
  line `(6) If the Board is also unable to accept the recommendation of the Broadcasting Council, it shall`
  line `record its reasons therefor and inform the Broadcasting Council accordingly.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (5) and (6), where the Broadcasting Council`
  line `deems it appropriate, it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, require the Corporation to broadcast its`
  line `recommendations with respect to a complaint in such manner as the Council may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (16382)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Transfer of certain assets, liabilities, etc., of Central Government to Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16382&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `As from`
  line `the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) all property and assets (including the Non-lapsable Fund) which immediately before that day`
  line `vested in the Central Government for the purpose of Akashvani or Doordarshan or both shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Corporation on such terms and conditions as may be determined by the Central`
  line `Government and the book value of all such property and assets shall be treated as the capital provided`
  line `by the Central Government to the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and`
  line `things engaged to be done by, with or for the Central Government immediately before such day for or`
  line `in connection with the purposes of Akashvani or Doordarshan or both shall be deemed to have been`
  line `incurred, entered into and engaged to be done by, with or for the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums of money due to the Central Government in relation to the Akashvani or Doordarshan`
  line `or both immediately before such day shall be deemed to be due to the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against the Central Government immediately before such day for any matter in relation to the`
  line `Akashvani or Doordarshan or both may be continued or instituted by or against the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (16383)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Grants, etc., by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16383&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of enabling the Corporation to`
  line `discharge its functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Corporation in each financial year,--`
  line
  line `(i) the proceeds of the broadcast receiver licence fees, if any, as reduced by the collection`
  line `charges; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such other sums of money as that Government considers necessary,`
  line
  line `by way of equity, grant-in-aid or loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (16384)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Fund of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16384&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall have its own Fund and all the receipts of the`
  line `Corporation (including the amounts which stand transferred to the Corporation under section 16) shall be`
  line `credited to the Fund and all payments by the Corporation shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the Fund shall be deposited in one or more nationalised banks in such`
  line `manner as the Corporation may decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "nationalised bank" means a corresponding new bank`
  line `specified in the First Schedule to the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970(5 of 1970) or a corresponding new bank specified in the First Schedule to the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980(40 of 1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (16385)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Investment of moneys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16385&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may invest its moneys in the securities of the Central`
  line `Government or any State Government or in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (16386)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Annual Financial Statement of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16386&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall prepare, in each`
  line `financial year, an Annual Financial Statement for the next financial year showing separately--`
  line
  line `(a) the expenditure which is proposed to be met from the internal resources of the Corporation;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the sums required from the Central Government to meet other expenses, and distinguishing--`
  line
  line `(i) revenue expenditure from other expenditure; and`
  line
  line `(ii) non-plan expenditure from plan expenditure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Annual Financial Statement shall be prepared in such form and forwarded at such time to the`
  line `Central Government for its approval as may be agreed to by that Government and the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (16387)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Accounts and audit of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16387&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall maintain proper accounts and`
  line `other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form and in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Corporation shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Corporation to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Corporation shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Corporation as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (16388)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Corporation not liable to be taxed.] Omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 163 (w.e.f.1-4-2003).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16388&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (16389)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16389&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time as and when occasion arises, issue to the Corporation such directions as it may think`
  line `necessary in the interests of the sovereignty, unity and integrity of India or the security of the State or`
  line `preservation of public order requiring it not to make a broadcast on a matter specified in the direction or`
  line `to make a broadcast on any matter of public importance specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Corporation makes a broadcast in pursuance of the direction issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the fact that such broadcast has been made in pursuance of such direction may also be`
  line `announced along with such broadcast, if the Corporation so desires.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every direction issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (16390)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Central Government to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16390&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may require`
  line `the Corporation to furnish such information as that Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (16391)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Report to Parliament in certain matters and recommendations as to action against the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16391&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Board persistently makes default in complying with any directions issued under`
  line `section 23 or fails to supply the information required under section 24, the Central Government may`
  line `prepare a report thereof and lay it before each House of Parliament for any recommendation thereof as to`
  line `any action(including super session of the Board) which may be taken against the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) On the recommendation of the Parliament, the President may by notification supersede the Board`
  line `for such period not exceeding six months as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing the notification under this sub-section, the President shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Board to show cause as to why it should not be superseded and shall consider`
  line `the explanations and objections, if any, of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon the publication of the notification under sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) all the Members shall, as from the date of super session, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Board, shall, until the Board is reconstituted under this`
  line `Act, be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the President may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) On the expiration of the period of super session specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (2), the President may reconstitute the Board by fresh appointments, and in such a case any`
  line `person who had vacated his office under clause (a) of sub-section (3) shall not be disqualified for`
  line `appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President may, at any time before the expiration of the period of super session, take`
  line `action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall cause the notification issued under sub-section (2)and a full report`
  line `of the action taken under this section to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (16392)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Office of member not to disqualify a Member of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16392&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that the`
  line `office of the member of the Broadcasting Council or of the Committee constituted under section 13 shall`
  line `not disqualify its holder for being chosen as, or for being, a Member of either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (16393)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Chairman, Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16393&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman and every other Member,`
  line `every officer or other employee of the Corporation and every member of a Committee thereof, the`
  line `President and every member of the Broadcasting Council or every member of a Regional Council or a`
  line `Recruitment Board shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code(45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (16394)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16394&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Corporation,the Chairman or any Member or officer or other employee thereof or the President or a`
  line `member of the Broadcasting Council or a member of a Regional Council or a Recruitment Board for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules on`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (16395)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16395&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of`
  line `the Corporation shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other Member authorised`
  line `by the Corporation in this behalf and all other instruments executed by the Corporation shall be`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Executive Member or by any officer of the Corporation authorised`
  line `by him in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (16396)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16396&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may, by general or special order, delegate to the`
  line `Chairman or any other Member or to any officer of the Corporation, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, if any, as may be specified therein, such of its powers and duties under this Act as it may`
  line `deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (16397)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16397&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall prepare once in every calendar year, in such form`
  line `and within such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a full account of its activities`
  line `(including the recommendations and suggestions made by the Broadcasting Council and the action taken`
  line `thereon) during the previous year and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and`
  line `that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Broadcasting Council shall prepare once in every calendar year, in such form and within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a full account of its activities during the previous year`
  line `and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the`
  line `same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (16398)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 2012, s. 3, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16398&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances and conditions of service in respect of leave, pension (if any),`
  line `provident fund and other matters in relation to the Whole-time Members under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the allowances payable to the Chairman and Part-time Members under sub-section (8) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the control, restrictions and conditions subject to which the Corporation may appoint officers`
  line `and other employees under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which and the conditions and restrictions subject to which a Recruitment Board`
  line `may be established under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the qualifications and other conditions of service of the members of a Recruitment Board and`
  line `their period of office under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `^1[(f) the terms and conditions of service in the Corporation of officers and employees under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11A;`
  line
  line `(ff) the manner and the terms and conditions subject to which matters relating to the posts borne`
  line `on the strength of the cadres of the Indian Information Service, the Central Secretariat Service or any`
  line `other cadre outside Akashvani or Doordarshan shall be determined under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11B;]`
  line
  line `(g) the salary and allowances and conditions of service in respect of leave, pension (if any),`
  line `provident fund and other matters in relation to the President of the Broadcasting Council under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) the allowances payable to other members of the Broadcasting Council and the members of the`
  line `Regional Councils, under sub-section (6) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which the Corporation may invest its moneys under section 19;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and the manner in which the annual statement of accounts shall be prepared under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(k) the form in which, and the time within which the Corporation and the Broadcasting Council`
  line `shall prepare their annual report under section 31;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (16399)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16399&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, by notification, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder for enabling it to perform its functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such regulations may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which and the purposes for which the Corporation may associate with itself any`
  line `person under sub-section (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the times and places at which meetings of the Board shall be held and, the procedure to be`
  line `followed thereat, and the quorum necessary for the transaction of the business at a meeting of the`
  line `Board under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the methods of recruitment and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the`
  line `Corporation under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `^1[(d) the conditions of service of officers and employees under sub-section (5) of section 11;]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) the services which may be provided by the Corporation under clause (f) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(g) the determination and levy of fees and other service charges in respect of advertisements and`
  line `other programmes under sub-section (7) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which and the period within which complaints may be made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter in respect of which provision is, in the opinion of the Corporation, necessary`
  line `for the performance of its functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the regulations under clause (c) or clause (d) shall be made only with the prior`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2012, s. 4, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (e) omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-3-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (16400)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16400&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (16401)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084&sectionId=16401&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00005_199025_1517807323084
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as it may deem necessary, for the removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
